t &= 6
\end{align*}

Substitute \( t = 6 \) back into one of the original equations to solve for \( u \):
\begin{align*}
2(6) - 4u &= 4 \\
12 - 4u &= 4 \\
-4u &= -8 \\
u &= 2
\end{align*}

Now we have \( t = 6 \) and \( u = 2 \). Substitute these back into either of the parameterizations to find the point of intersection.

